+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ebmi8sGe8TNR7uLrwxk2RN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Reactive Spreadsheet Engine\n     2→\n     3→Build a spreadsheet engine as a TypeScript library. The engine manages a grid of cells that can contain values or formulas, with automatic reactive updates when dependencies change.\n     4→\n     5→## Cell References\n     6→\n     7→Cells are referenced by column letter(s) followed by a row number: `A1`, `B2`, `Z100`, `AA1`, etc. Columns use letters A-Z, then AA-AZ, BA-BZ, etc. Rows are 1-based integers.\n     8→\n     9→## Cell Values\n    10→\n    11→A cell can contain:\n    12→- **Numbers**: `42`, `3.14`\n    13→- **Strings**: `\"hello\"` (text values)\n    14→- **Booleans**: `true`, `false`\n    15→- **Formulas**: expressions starting with `=` (e.g., `=A1+B1`, `=SUM(A1:A5)`)\n    16→\n    17→## Formulas\n    18→\n    19→Formulas begin with `=` and support:\n    20→- **Arithmetic operators**: `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`\n    21→- **Parentheses** for grouping: `=(A1+B1)*2`\n    22→- **Cell references**: `=A1`, `=B2+C3`\n    23→- **Comparison operators**: `>`, `<`, `>=`, `<=`, `=`, `<>` (used in IF conditions)\n    24→\n    25→## Built-in Functions\n    26→\n    27→- `SUM(range)` — sum of all numeric values in the range\n    28→- `AVERAGE(range)` — arithmetic mean of numeric values in the range\n    29→- `MIN(range)` — smallest numeric value in the range\n    30→- `MAX(range)` — largest numeric value in the range\n    31→- `COUNT(range)` — count of numeric values in the range\n    32→- `IF(condition, trueValue, falseValue)` — conditional expression\n    33→\n    34→## Ranges\n    35→\n    36→Ranges are specified as `start:end`:\n    37→- **Column range**: `A1:A5` — cells A1, A2, A3, A4, A5\n    38→- **Row range**: `A1:C1` — cells A1, B1, C1\n    39→- **Block range**: `A1:C3` — all cells in the 2D rectangle from A1 to C3\n    40→\n    41→## Reactive Updates\n    42→\n    43→When a cell's value changes, all cells that depend on it (directly or transitively) must automatically recompute. For example, if `B1` contains `=A1+1` and `A1` changes from `5` to `10`, then `B1` should automatically update from `6` to `11`.\n    44→\n    45→## Circular Reference Detection\n    46→\n    47→If setting a cell would create a circular dependency (e.g., `A1=B1` and `B1=A1`), the engine must detect this and throw an error. This includes indirect cycles through any number of intermediate cells.\n    48→\n    49→## API\n    50→\n    51→Export a `Spreadsheet` class (or equivalent) from `src/index.ts` with the following interface:\n    52→\n    53→```typescript\n    54→class Spreadsheet {\n    55→  // Set a cell's value. Can be a raw value or a formula string starting with '='\n    56→  set(cell: string, value: string | number | boolean): void;\n    57→\n    58→  // Get a cell's computed value. Returns null for empty cells.\n    59→  get(cell: string): string | number | boolean | null;\n    60→\n    61→  // Get the display string for a cell's computed value.\n    62→  getDisplay(cell: string): string;\n    63→\n    64→  // Get all non-empty cells as a Map from cell reference to computed value.\n    65→  getCells(): Map<string, any>;\n    66→}\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→## Example Usage\n    70→\n    71→```typescript\n    72→const sheet = new Spreadsheet();\n    73→\n    74→sheet.set('A1', 10);\n    75→sheet.set('A2', 20);\n    76→sheet.set('A3', '=A1+A2');\n    77→sheet.get('A3');        // 30\n    78→sheet.getDisplay('A3'); // \"30\"\n    79→\n    80→sheet.set('A1', 50);\n    81→sheet.get('A3');        // 70  (reactively updated)\n    82→\n    83→sheet.set('B1', '=SUM(A1:A2)');\n    84→sheet.get('B1');        // 70\n    85→\n    86→sheet.set('C1', '=IF(A1>30, \"big\", \"small\")');\n    87→sheet.get('C1');        // \"big\"\n    88→```\n    89→\n    90→## Requirements\n    91→\n    92→- Implement in TypeScript with proper types\n    93→- Export from `src/index.ts`\n    94→- Write tests using Vitest\n    95→- All code in the `src/` directory\n    96→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fh6P4HGZDY6UYtxauLHyoe","session_id":"4b8053d3-cefb-4b9e-83d3-31438fe4b3bd","uuid":"2bfa259a-3c1e-4ef9-9d08-8903a2b4fc36"}
