+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BEejZjsKN3ppETNtETUHrM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DDV4PZ1vF9S9gZMB1XpGYv","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"OUTPUT=$(gemini -p 'Implement a reactive spreadsheet engine in a single file src/index.ts. This is a TypeScript library (strict mode, ES2022, Node16 module).\n\nRequirements:\n1. Export a class named Spreadsheet with these methods:\n   - set(cell: string, value: string | number | boolean): void - sets raw values or formula strings starting with \"=\"\n   - get(cell: string): string | number | boolean | null - returns computed value, null for empty\n   - getDisplay(cell: string): string - returns display string of computed value (empty string for null)\n   - getCells(): Map<string, any> - returns all non-empty cells mapped to computed values\n\n2. Cell references: column letter(s) + row number. A=0, B=1, ..., Z=25, AA=26, AB=27 etc. Row is 1-based. Parse case-insensitively (store uppercase).\n\n3. Cell values can be: numbers (42, 3.14), strings (\"hello\" - stored without quotes), booleans (true/false), formulas (strings starting with \"=\").\n\n4. Formula parser: Build a recursive descent parser that tokenizes and parses formulas into an AST. Support:\n   - Number literals, string literals (in double quotes), boolean literals\n   - Cell references (A1, AA1, etc.)\n   - Ranges (A1:C3) - only valid as function arguments\n   - Binary operators: +, -, *, / with correct precedence (*/higher than +-)\n   - Unary minus: -A1, -(1+2)\n   - Comparison operators: >, <, >=, <=, = (equals), <> (not equals) - lowest precedence\n   - Parentheses for grouping\n   - Function calls: SUM, AVERAGE, MIN, MAX, COUNT, IF\n\n5. Built-in functions:\n   - SUM(range_or_values) - sum numeric values. Range expands to all cells in rectangle.\n   - AVERAGE(range_or_values) - mean of numeric values\n   - MIN(range_or_values) - smallest numeric value\n   - MAX(range_or_values) - largest numeric value  \n   - COUNT(range_or_values) - count of numeric values\n   - IF(condition, trueValue, falseValue) - conditional\n\n6. Ranges: A1:A5 (column), A1:C1 (row), A1:C3 (block). Expand to list of cell refs covering the rectangle.\n\n7. Dependency tracking: When a formula is set, extract all cell references it depends on. Store a dependency graph (Map<string, Set<string>> for dependents). When a cell changes, topologically recompute all transitive dependents.\n\n8. Circular reference detection: Before accepting a formula, check if it would create a cycle. If so, throw an Error with message containing \"Circular\". Do NOT set the cell if circular.\n\n9. Reactive updates: When set() is called, after updating the cell, find all transitive dependents using the dependency graph, topologically sort them, and recompute each in order.\n\n10. When a cell is set to a new value/formula, remove old dependencies before adding new ones.\n\nConstraints:\n- Language: TypeScript strict mode\n- Dependencies: NO external packages, stdlib only\n- Single file: src/index.ts\n- Export the Spreadsheet class as a named export\n- All types must be explicit, no \"any\" in function signatures (internal any is ok for cell storage)\n- Output ONLY the TypeScript code. No markdown fences. No explanation.' -o text 2>&1)\necho \"$OUTPUT\"","description":"Gemini CLI: generate spreadsheet engine","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":20783,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b8053d3-cefb-4b9e-83d3-31438fe4b3bd","uuid":"b2e50d5e-32ff-408b-b604-1716539a7bec"}
